you have that single axial substituent move on to.";i:1;s:82:"Alternate your axial substituents up and down all the way around your cyclohexane.";i:2;s:43:"Every carbon on the chair conformation has.";i:3;s:165:"The A-value of a tert-Butyl is in the range of 5 kcalmol which is around the value of the energy difference between cyclohexane in twist-boat and chair conformation.";i:4;s:168:"Ive drawn cis-14-di-tert-butyl-cyclohexane with ChemDraw and used EditGet 3D Model and ChemBioDraw gave me the structure which is NOT the energetical most suitable one.";i:5;s:111:"To begin start by drawing two lines that are parallel to each other but not perfectly horizontal as shown here.";i:6;s:76:"Next add a downward-pointing V tip to one end this is the tail of the chair.";i:7;s:84:"Finally add an upward-pointing V tip to the other end this is the nose of the chair.";i:8;s:68:"The steps involved in drawing the chair conformation of cyclohexane.";i:9;s:109:"In a chair conformation with a few exceptions only axial substituents will give rise to steric strain energy.";i:10;s:44:"This is true for 1R-33-dichlorocyclohexanol.";i:11;s:95:"In each of the conformations drawn in step 4 circle the axial substituents other than hydrogen.";i:12;s:91:"Click the structures and reaction arrows to view the 3D models and animations respectively.";i:13;s:111:"Cyclic alkanes can also interconvert between their conformers by rotation of the single carbon to carbon bonds.";i:14;s:40:"Structure and conformations of decalins.";i:15;s:28:"Converting Haworth to Chair.";i:16;s:100:"The final piece of these conversions is often to draw a complete chair conformation of the pyranose.";i:17;s:137:"The trick is to remember that just like the Haworth projections the chair conformations also have the well-defined up and down positions.";i:18;s:117:"- The high-energy intermediate conformation of cyclohexane as it converts from one chair conformation into the other.";i:19;s:121:"- footrest flips upward forms the 