 lines so the top horizontal dotted line is.";i:36;s:83:"Draw the two possible chair conformations for cis-1-tert-butyl-3-methylcyclohexane.";i:37;s:137:"Draw a Newman projection for the most stable of the two conformations and provide an explanation of why that conformation is more stable.";i:38;s:83:"Draw the two possible chair conformations for cis-1-tert-butyl-3-methylcyclohexane.";i:39;s:14:"Draw a Newman.";i:40;s:95:"Drawing the cyclohexane chair conformations adds unnecessary stress to most chemistry students.";i:41;s:154:"Follow the steps below to easily draw the chair conformation and ring flips like a pro so you can focus your mental energy on solving the reaction itself.";i:42;s:66:"Consider The Pocket Chemist to help get your homework done faster.";i:43;s:96:"Although it is more stable the chair conformation is much more rigid than the boat conformation.";i:44;s:40:"The boat conformation is quite flexible.";i:45;s:168:"By flexing to a new formthe twist conformation Fig5the boat conformation can relieve some of its torsional strain and at the same time reduce the flagpole interactions.";i:46;s:72:"It is the only conformation that leads to all staggered dihedral angles.";i:47;s:94:"A dihedral angle is one where there are four atoms connected together and under consideration.";i:48;s:79:"When the 2nd and 3rd act as the axis of rotation the 1st and 4th can become cl.";i:49;s:52:"The chair conformation is the most stable conformer.";i:50;s:80:"At 25 C 9999 of all molecules in a cyclohexane solution adopt this conformation.";i:51;s:21:"The symmetry is D 3d.";i:52;s:34:"All carbon centers are equivalent.";i:53;s:138:"Six hydrogen centers are poised in axial positions roughly parallel with the C 3 axis and six hydrogen atoms are located near the equator.";i:54;s:66:"Cyclohexane has two limiting conformations the chair and the boat.";i:55;s:73:"The boat conformation is much less stable than the chair for two reasons.";i:56;s:241:"Firstly Newman projections along 